$ /sys/bus

`/sys/bus` is a directory for the available bus types (PCI, IDE, USB) in the kernel.

Each directory under `/sys/bus` contains at least the following two subdirectories:
  • `/sys/bus/XXX/devices` and
  • `/sys/bus/XXX/drivers`.

Directories I've found under `/sys/bus` include:
